The paper discusses the detection of covert channels in cloud environments using machine learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms for this purpose suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of a framework for monitoring cloud applications, which may be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of SVMs for handling large datasets, which may be relevant to networked systems (cs.NI).
